West Bengal
Nov 11, 2014
Murder, Crime
Description:
			A woman was hacked to death and her husband seriously injured by a group of about eight people at Jhaudanga, police said today.

Aparna Ghosh (45) and her husband Buddhadev Ghosh were attacked with knives and lathis by a group of about eight people in their residence last night. Aparna died on the spot. Their son managed to escape the spot.

Buddhadev was hospitalised aand an FIR naming eight persons lodged this morning.

Old enmity could be the reason for the attack, police said.


